body_html:
Same problem using today's head.

Looking at the failure, it happens in pywrap_tensorflow_internal.py trying to load __pywrap_tensorflow_internal module. I did a search and there's no file called _pywrap_tensorflow_internal that was included in wheel installation

The problem is in this block of pywrap_tensorflow_internal.py

      try:
            fp, pathname, description = imp.find_module('_pywrap_tensorflow_internal', [dirname(__file__)])

This is the wheel that got built (Ubuntu 14.04, Python 3)
https://storage.cloud.google.com/tensorflow-community-wheels/mar5.xla.tensorflow-1.0.0-cp35-cp35m-linux_x86_64.whl

body:
Same problem using today's head.

Looking at the failure, it happens in `pywrap_tensorflow_internal.py` trying to load `__pywrap_tensorflow_internal` module. I did a search and there's no file called `_pywrap_tensorflow_internal` that was included in wheel installation

The problem is in this block of `pywrap_tensorflow_internal.py`
```
      try:
            fp, pathname, description = imp.find_module('_pywrap_tensorflow_internal', [dirname(__file__)])

```
This is the wheel that got built (Ubuntu 14.04, Python 3)
https://storage.cloud.google.com/tensorflow-community-wheels/mar5.xla.tensorflow-1.0.0-cp35-cp35m-linux_x86_64.whl
